luding athletics, badminton and boxing.\", \"from\": 951, \"to\": 1123, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Afghanistan is represented by a contingent of three women and three men, in a largely symbolic move by the International Olympic Committee as a message to the country, which under Taliban rule has restricted women's and girls' access to sports and gyms.\", \"from\": 1125, \"to\": 1378, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1125, \"end\": 1136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9480055206003263, \"rank\": 0.05484599052287684, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}, {\"begin\": 1232, \"end\": 1263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1305, \"end\": 1312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\", \"score\": 0.9350059972730628, \"rank\": 0.06911846714699994, \"text\": \"Taliban\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both the head of Afghanistan's national Olympic committee (NOC) recognized by the IOC and its secretary general are currently in exile.\", \"from\": 1380, \"to\": 1515, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1397, \"end\": 1408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9480055206003263, \"rank\": 0.05484599052287684, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}, {\"begin\": 1411, \"end\": 1443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natio